ult_available":"1 result is available: {{suggestion}}.","news_vj_search_lookup_multiple_results_available":"{{numberOfResults}} results are available.","news_vj_search_lookup_selected_result":"{{suggestion}} is selected.","show_results":"TRUE","show_all_candidates":"TRUE","show_ni_candidates":"TRUE","title":"Is there an election in my area?","search_cta":"Enter your postcode, or the name of your English, Scottish or Welsh council area or Northern Ireland constituency to find out.","title_results":"Who won in my area?","search_cta_results":"Enter your postcode, or the name of your English, Scottish or Welsh council area or Northern Ireland constituency to find out.","search_submit_check":"Please enter a valid UK postcode, or search by the English, Scottish or Welsh council area or Northern Ireland constituency","search_fail":"Sorry, we can't find that area. Please try searching by postcode, English, Scottish or Welsh council area or Northern Ireland constituency","noJS":"A modern browser with JavaScript and a stable internet connection is required to view this interactive. [More information about these elections](https://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/who-we-are-and-what-we-do/elections-and-referendums/upcoming-elections)","refresh_text":"Refresh the page to load the latest results","":"","num_of_votes_text":"In {{name}}, voting will take place on {{beginBold}}Thursday 5 May{{endBold}} for the following:","no_votes_text":"There are no main council or mayoral elections in {{name}} in May. There may be parish council elections or council by-elections where you are. Check your local council website for full details.","num_of_votes_text_results":"In {{name}}, voting took place on Thursday 5 May for the following:","no_votes_text_results":"There were no main council or mayoral elections in {{name}} in May.  There may have been parish council elections or council by-elections where you are. Check your local council website for full details. ","more_info_text":"","more_info_text_ni":"[More on Northern Ireland politics](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/northern_ireland/northern_ireland_politics)","more_info_text_eng":"","more_info_text_wal":"[Wales elections: A simple guide](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-politics-60736735)","more_info_text_scot":"[Scotland elections: A simple guide](https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-60764222)","disclaimer_text":"Note: This lookup covers the national election in Northern Ireland, as well as council and mayoral elections in England, Scotland and Wales. There may be parish council elections or council by-elections where you are. Check your local council website for full details.","last_updated":"Last updated: {{timestamp}}","timeline_current":"2022","timeline_previous":"Previous","ignore ":"CONTEXTUAL INFORMATION","contextual_title":"What do they do?","contextual_text_bristol":"What is it about?","district_council":"District councils are responsible for services like bin collections, parks, public housing and local planning applications.<br/><br/>Other public services in a district council area will be controlled by the county council which covers a wider area.","county_council":"County councils are responsible for services like education, road maintenance, social care, public libraries and long-term strategic planning.<br/><br/>Other public services in a county council area will be controlled by the more local district council.","unitary_authority":"Unitary authorities look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care.","unitary_authority_ny":"Unitary authorities look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care<br/><br/>North Yorkshire Council is a new council that will come into existence on the 1 April 2023. It replaces North Yorkshire County Council and the district councils of Craven, Hambleton, Harrogate, Richmondshire, Ryedale, Scarborough and Selby.","unitary_authority_som":"Unitary authorities look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care<br/><br/>Somerset Council is a new council that will come into existence on the 1 April 2023. It replaces Somerset County Council and the district councils of Mendip, Sedgemoor, South Somerset and Somerset West and Taunton.","unitary_authority_cum":"Unitary authorities look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care<br/><br/>Cumberland Council is a new council that will come into existence on the 1 April 2023. It replaces Cumbria County Council and the district councils of Allerdale, Carlisle and Copeland.","unitary_authority_wf":"Unitary authorities look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care<br/><br/>Westmorland and Furness Council is a new council that will come into existence on the 1 April 2023. It replaces Cumbria County Council and the district councils of Barrow, Eden and South Lakeland.","london_borough":"London borough councils look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care.","metropolitan_borough":"Metropolitan borough councils look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care.","scottish_council":"Scottish councils look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care.","welsh_council":"Welsh councils look after all the local council services, such as schools, road maintenance, bin collections, public housing and social care.","city_mayor":"The council mayor is the directly elected leader of a council.<br/><br/>They are responsible for all of the services controlled by the council and appoint members of the cabinet who each have responsibility for specific council services.","combined_authority_mayor":"The combined authority mayor is responsible for planning and strategy for regional transport, skills training and local economic development across several local authorities.","westminster_constituency":"MPs split their time between working in Parliament and working in their constituency - the area they represent in Parliament.<br/><br/>When they are working in their constituency they will often hold meetings called surgeries, where local people can attend to discuss issues important to them.<br/><br/>When MPs are working in Parliament they can raise these issues with other MPs or government ministers, as well as suggest and vote on new laws.","ni_constituency":"The Northern Ireland Assembly is responsible for services such as justice and policing, health, education, housing and the environment in Northern Ireland.<br/><br/>The UK government is still responsible for issues such as income tax rates, foreign affairs and defence.<br/><br/>Five Members of the Legislative Assembly are elected to represent each of the 18 Assembly constituencies using a system of proportional representation called the single transferable vote.","mayor_ref":"Bristol City Council held a referendum on how the council is run. 59.3% voted for a committee model of governance where the party with a majority of councillors runs the council. 40.7% voted for the current system of a directly elected mayor who appoints a cabinet. ","find_out_more":"More about the candidates","find_out_more_candidates":"See full list of candidates","candidates_intro":"These are the candidates for your area","parties_intro":"These are the parties for your area","party":"Party","candidate":"Candidate","results_one-winner":"The winning candidate is:","results_ni-winners":"The winning candidates are:","results_pending":"Awaiting result","results_link-text":"See full results","seats":"Seats","change":